{"title_page": "Lake Botos", "text_new": "{{short description|Lake in Costa Rica}}\n{{Infobox lake\n| name = Lake Botos\n| type = [[Volcanic crater lake|crater lake]]\n| image = Volcan Poas Laguna Botos.JPG\n| caption = \n| pushpin_map = Costa Rica\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location in Costa Rica\n| coordinates = {{coord|10.187086|N|84.227267|W|region:CR_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}}\n| area = {{convert|0.1033|km2|abbr=on}}\n| length = {{convert|365|m|mi|abbr=on}}\n| max-depth = {{convert|9|m|abbr=on}}\n| volume = \n| residence_time = \n| shore = \n| elevation = {{convert|2580|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| islands = \n| cities = \n}}\n\n'''Lake Botos''' ({{lang-es|Laguna Botos}}), is a [[Volcanic crater lake|crater lake]] located inside the [[Po\u00e1s Volcano National Park]].<ref name=\"umana\">{{cite journal |last1=Uma\u00f1a V. |first1=Gerardo |title=Limnology of Botos Lake, a tropical crater lake in Costa Rica |journal=Revista Biolog\u00eda Tropical |date=2001 |volume=39 |issue=2 |accessdate=13 April 2020 |url=https://revistas.ucr.ac.cr/index.php/rbt/article/view/26288/26495}}</ref>.\n\n== Location ==\n\nIt is located in [[Alajuela Province|Alajuela]] province of [[Costa Rica]]. \n\n== Physical aspects ==\n\nLake Botos is located within Botos cone crater, it has an almost circular outline. It is around 7,540 years old, drains through Angel River, and surrounding forest is classified as tropical, subtropical and some [[p\u00e1ramo]] vegetation. There are around 23 algae species.<ref name=\"umana\"></ref>\n\n== Social and economic uses ==\n\nAs part of the Po\u00e1s Volcano National Park, this lake benefits the tourism industry.{{Citation needed}} Access pathways are paved and the viewpoint is easily accessed.{{Citation needed}}\n\n== Gallery ==\n[[File:Panorama 2 Botos Lake (Crater), Poas Volcano Ntl Park CRI 08 2009.jpg|center|thumb|650px|Lake Botos panorama as seen from the viewpoint trail]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of lakes in Costa Rica]]\n* [[List of volcanoes in Costa Rica]]\n\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Geography of Alajuela Province]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Alajuela Province]]\n[[Category:Lakes of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Volcanic crater lakes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Lake in Costa Rica}}\n{{Infobox lake\n| name = Lake Botos\n| type = [[Volcanic crater lake|crater lake]]\n| image = Volcan Poas Laguna Botos.JPG\n| caption = \n| pushpin_map = Costa Rica\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location in Costa Rica\n| coordinates = {{coord|10.187086|N|84.227267|W|region:CR_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}}\n| area = {{convert|0.1033|km2|abbr=on}}\n| length = {{convert|365|m|mi|abbr=on}}\n| max-depth = {{convert|9|m|abbr=on}}\n| volume = \n| residence_time = \n| shore = \n| elevation = {{convert|2580|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| islands = \n| cities = \n}}\n\n'''Lake Botos''' ({{lang-es|Laguna Botos}}), is a [[Volcanic crater lake|crater lake]] located inside the [[Po\u00e1s Volcano National Park]].<ref name=\"umana\">{{cite journal |last1=Uma\u00f1a V. |first1=Gerardo |title=Limnology of Botos Lake, a tropical crater lake in Costa Rica |journal=Revista Biolog\u00eda Tropical |date=2001 |volume=39 |issue=2 |accessdate=13 April 2020 |url=https://revistas.ucr.ac.cr/index.php/rbt/article/view/26288/26495}}</ref>.\n\n== Location ==\n\nIt is located in [[Alajuela Province|Alajuela]] province of [[Costa Rica]]. \n\n== Physical aspects ==\n\nLake Botos is located within Botos cone crater, it has an almost circular outline. It is around 7,540 years old, drains through Angel River, and surrounding forest is classified as tropical, subtropical and some [[p\u00e1ramo]] vegetation. There are around 23 algae species.<ref name=\"umana\"></ref>\n\n== Social and economic uses ==\n\nAs part of the Po\u00e1s Volcano National Park, this lake benefits the tourism industry.{{Citation needed}} Access pathways are paved and the viewpoint is easily accessed.{{Citation needed}}\n\n== Gallery ==\n[[File:Panorama 2 Botos Lake (Crater), Poas Volcano Ntl Park CRI 08 2009.jpg|center|thumb|650px|Lake Botos panorama as seen from the viewpoint trail]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of lakes in Costa Rica]]\n* [[List of volcanoes in Costa Rica]]\n\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Geography of Alajuela Province]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Alajuela Province]]\n[[Category:Lakes of Costa Rica]]\n", "name_user": "MrClog", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:Volcanic crater lakesusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Botos"}
